threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a highly sophisticated modular Linux backdoor and rootkit. It features extensive stealth capabilities including the deployment of eBPF programs to hide PIDs, network ports, and files from system monitoring tools. It implements process masquerading to appear as legitimate system daemons (e.g., dbus-broker, rsyslogd, crond) and utilizes anti-analysis techniques to detect debuggers and Frida. Core malicious behaviors include encrypted Command and Control (C2) over HTTPS/WebSockets (associated with IP 8.149.128.10), credential harvesting from shell history and SSH configs, lateral movement discovery in Kubernetes environments, and the ability to execute remote plugins for container escape or persistence. It further ensures operational security by clearing HISTFILE and using a custom reverse shell ('PipeShell').
